# Cursor Rules for DearHour (모바일 청첩장 서비스)

## Project Context
This is a mobile invitation/wedding card builder service built with:
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript 5 (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS 4
- Prisma 6 + Supabase Postgres
- Zustand for state management
- Supabase Auth for authentication

## Language
- Always respond in Korean (한국어로 응답)
- Code comments in English, UI text in Korean

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use explicit types, never `any`
- Prefer `interface` for objects, `type` for unions/intersections
- Use optional chaining (`?.`) and nullish coalescing (`??`)
- All functions must have explicit return types for exports

### React Components
- Use function declarations, not arrow functions for components
- Props interface must be separate from component
- Server Components by default, `"use client"` only when needed
- Event handlers: `handle*` for functions, `on*` for props

### File Organization
- Page components: `app/[route]/page.tsx`
- Client components: `app/[route]/*-client.tsx`
- API routes: `app/api/[endpoint]/route.ts`
- Shared components: `components/`
- Feature-specific: `features/[feature]/`

### Tailwind CSS
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Class order: layout → box model → typography → color → effects
- Prefer Tailwind classes over arbitrary values
- Use project color palette (gray-50/100/200, black/white for buttons)

### API Routes
- Always validate input
- Use try-catch with proper error responses
- Apply rate limiting for public endpoints
- Return structured JSON: `{ data }` or `{ error, code? }`

### Database (Prisma)
- Use `select` to fetch only needed fields
- Use transactions for related operations
- Add indexes for frequently queried fields

## Prohibited
- `any` type
- `// @ts-ignore`
- Inline styles (use Tailwind)
- console.log in production code
- Hardcoded sensitive values

## External Integrations
When working with external services (Supabase, Toss Payments, Naver Maps):
- Check AGENTS.md for existing integrations first
- Don't ask to reconfigure completed integrations
- Report runtime errors with specific details

## Git
- Commit messages: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` in Korean
- Push immediately when user requests commit/push
- Don't ask for confirmation before push
